This paper involves the use of genetic algorithms to evolve animats equipped with Markov Brains, which suggests a focus on neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.NE, cs.AI). The animats are performing a spatial navigation task, which involves robotics and control (cs.RO, cs.SY). The paper also discusses the social behavior of the evolved swarms, which could fall under machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
